# Affected Package Builds

By default, validate code changes by building only the package or packages affected by the edit.

- Use package-level scripts such as `pnpm build:core`, `pnpm build:app`, `pnpm build:cli`, `pnpm build:server`, `pnpm build:extension`, or `pnpm build:mcp-server` when the touched files map cleanly to one package.
- If a package has no root script, use `pnpm --filter <workspace-package-name> build`.
- Build dependencies first when the affected package depends on another changed workspace package.
- Run full `pnpm build` only when the change affects shared contracts, workspace dependencies, root build configuration, lockfiles, or multiple packages where the impact is unclear.
- In final responses, state which package-level build was run, or explain why a full build was necessary.
